    "faq_section_j83j4h": {
      "type": "faq-section",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_Lpi8dA": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What is the most popular cut of engagement ring? ",
            "faq_answer": "<p>The Round cut remains the most popular choice globally due to its unmatched sparkle and versatility. However, Oval and Cushion cuts are rapidly growing in popularity for modern brides.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_4qiqNh": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Which cut is best in diamonds?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>\"Best\" is subjective! If you want the most sparkle, the Round Brilliant is scientifically cut to reflect the most light. If you want the best clarity and elegance, the Emerald cut is superior. If you want the best value for size, the Marquise or Pear often looks largest.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_Q6dc3t": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What metals are the best for engagement rings?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>Platinum and 14k or 18k Gold (White, Yellow, or Rose) are the best metals. Platinum is the most durable and hypoallergenic, while Gold offers a classic warmth. White gold is a popular choice to keep the diamond looking icy white.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_VTebkY": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "What is a perfect engagement ring?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>A perfect engagement ring is one that suits your partner's personal style, fits their lifestyle, and fits within your budget. There is no single \"perfect\" ring, only the one that perfectly symbolizes your relationship.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_qLTfr7": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Which color diamond is best?",
            "faq_answer": "<p>For white diamonds, the \"Colorless\" range (grades D, E, F) is considered the best and rarest. However, \"Near Colorless\" (G, H, I) diamonds offer incredible value and look white to the naked eye once set in a ring.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_item_bmNycT": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "faq_question": "Which diamond is high quality? ",
            "faq_answer": "<p>A high-quality diamond is defined by the 4Cs: Cut, Color, Clarity, and Carat. A diamond with an \"Excellent\" or \"Ideal\" cut grade will always look higher quality because it sparkles more, hiding minor inclusions or color tints. At Lucira, we prioritize the Cut grade to ensure maximum beauty.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
